Ask HN: What are your thought about emoji on work slack messages?
text: Every now and then I realise I overuse my emoji in many sentences at work, I think it is because when I communicate in real life, I am quite expressive so when typing in slack or communicate over texting platform, I have the tendency to insert emoji into my messages... I find it becoming a concern lately as I look back at some conversations and noticed there is an emoji in almost every 2 sentences I sent.. :scream: <-- case in point. :(

Show HN: An HTML endless runner under 900 lines without frameworks or libraries
text: My wife and I recently submitted to a mobile game jam on Newgrounds (yes, it's still around). What started as a question of whether we could do it somehow morphed into whether we could do without so many of the seemingly needless complications rampant in our respective industries. My wife thus did all the art as traditional frame-by-frame animation (no puppets or tweening) and I preceded without a game engine. I did use a pre-processor that gives JS a Lisp syntax (Parenscript), because C-syntax is gross. We hope the end result, while definitely of small scope, will serve to inspire some thought as to what is and isn't needed in your next project.
